<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2a6b1963bdcbb1f5bc0e68e6c2f18651?s=48&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' /></div>	
<div class="comment-body"><span class="time">August 27th, 2009 at 8:55 pm </span>
<p class="byline"><strong>Tara</strong></p>
<p>I recently started dressing up, wearing skirts and boots [gifts I had received last xmas and finally started wearing], flowy tops from salvation army and ballet flats over skater shoes. People keep asking me if I&#8217;m going to party/bar/fancy restaurant or why I dress up, I just smile and say I do it for me. To which they usually stare at me like I sprouted a second head, and I move on. I&#8217;ve had a lot more confidence, standing straighter, and being more outgoing since changing from sweats/yoga pants/hoodies/sneakers to dresses/leggings/skinny jeans and prettier tops. I didn&#8217;t think clothes would affect my attitude so much, I even find it easier to do presentations.</p>
</div>
