<p>I have dresses that were for special occasions, but I dress them down with flat leather sandals so that I can wear them on the weekends during the day, too. I hate the fact that I spent, in some cases, over $200 for dresses that are only &#8220;dress up.&#8221; Forget it! Some sandals, a cardigan, or shawl and it&#8217;s casual.</p>
<p>When I lived in California, it wasn&#8217;t unusual that people would dress up. Now I live in Arkansas where, as you&#8217;ve described, everyone where&#8217;s sweat pants and hoodies. One woman, I know, is the epitome of frump. She&#8217;s been wearing the same sweatpants and hoodie for years, and sometimes everyday.</p>
